    <tax:treatment obkms_id="936d2e3e-f0e5-4b4a-8ee3-1ddca8c8c7dc" obkms_process="TRUE">
      <tax:nomenclature obkms_id="88cee0da-29c0-4ef2-bcca-2296925c2b9e" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:name obkms_id="71f472b3-266e-4459-89c9-7e991e5afd05" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Arachnida</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Araneae</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Zoropsidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Devendra</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>saama</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank><dwc:scientificNameAuthorship>Polotow &amp; Griswold, 2017</dwc:scientificNameAuthorship></tax:xmldata>Devendra saama</tax:name><tax:status>sp. nov.</tax:status>Figures 13A–C,14</tax:nomenclature>
      <tax:div type="materials_examined" obkms_id="30cd31ae-4b09-438f-8a82-6ea469299a79" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>
          <tax:collection_event><tax:xmldata><dwc:Country>Sri Lanka</dwc:Country><dwc:Locality>Kandy</dwc:Locality><dwc:TypeStatus>holotype</dwc:TypeStatus></tax:xmldata>Type material. Female holotype from Kandy , Sri Lanka , # 18302, deposited in MNHN .</tax:collection_event>
        </tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="etymology">
        <tax:p>Etymology. The species name is a noun in apposition taken from the Sinhalese word for “peace.”</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="diagnosis" obkms_id="836d01a1-8519-4ddc-874b-45b28fec3c60" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Diagnosis. Females can be diagnosed from female of other<tax:name obkms_id="db1352f2-8789-4c30-aa63-5be904cd270a" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Arachnida</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Araneae</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Zoropsidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Devendra</dwc:Genus><dwc:taxonRank>genus</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Devendra</tax:name> species by having the epigynum without a developed median lobe (Fig. 13A), and the vulva with the head of the spermathecae sessile on the main spermathecae and the fertilization ducts arising from a short tube (Fig. 13B, C).</tax:p>
        <tax:p>DesCription. Female (holotype): Total length 5.17. Markings as inFig. 9A. Carapace 2.42 long, 1.67 wide, 0.96 high; clypeus 0.07 high. Eye diameters: AME 0.07, ALE 0.10, PME 0.10, PLE 0.10. Chelicerae 1.08 long; sternum 1.06 long, 0.92 wide; labium 0.40 long; palpal coxae 0.72 long. Spination as in genus description. Leg measurements (Femur + Patella + Tibia + Metatarsus + Tarsus = [Total]): I: 1.50 + 0.75 + 0.56 + 0.54 + 0.44 = 3.79; II: 1.37 + 0.71 + 1.00 + 0.96 + 0.83 = 4.87; III: 0.88 + 0.50 + 0.83 + 1.25 + 0.83 = 4.29; IV: 1.75 + 0.62 + 1.37 + 2.08 + 1.12 = 6.44. Leg formula 4123. Epigynum: subtriangular epigynal plate; transverse fold dividing median lobe and lateral lobes (Fig. 13A, B). Spermathecae oval with an apical glandular opening (Fig. 13C).</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="description">
        <tax:p>Male. Unknown.</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="materials_examined" obkms_id="54ecea52-a0df-44a2-b086-2ba490f409d9" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Material examined. Only the type.</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
      <tax:div type="distribution" obkms_id="a8d2d0de-5813-40e9-965c-94224a3c5733" obkms_process="TRUE">
        <tax:p>Distribution. Known only from thetype locality at Kandy inSri Lanka (Fig. 14).</tax:p>
      </tax:div>
